<p>
  Join us in this third and final session – focused on persistent identifiers –
  of a 3-part series to explore the NHMRC/MRFF Open Science Policy and its
  impact on the research community.
</p>
<p>
  RAiD will be presenting at the Open Science Conference 2026. Visit our booth
  and attend our session on persistent identification for research projects.
  This is an opportunity to meet the RAiD team, see live demonstrations, and
  discuss how RAiD can work within your institution.
</p>
<ul>
  <li>Date: 3–5 June 2026</li>
  <li>Location: Melbourne Convention and Exhibition Centre, Melbourne, Australia</li>
  <li>RAiD session: 4 June 2026, 2:00 PM AEST</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Conference registration details are available on the event website.
